Had the most fantastic dinner and service last night with my wife and friends at Tommy V's Urban Kitchen.
Our waiter, Robert, was excellent and the owner Zoran was attentive and very friendly.
Our dinners were fantastic.
I had the halibut and my wife had the Chilean bass.
Both dishes were delicious and beautifully presented and served at prefect serving temperatures.
The fingerling potatoe sides were also wonderful and the beet salad that my wife and shared was delicious.
My friend who loves short ribs ordered them and raved about how good they were - generous portion also.
All in all, one of the best local dinners we've enjoyed in Scottsdale in quite some time and at a price that won't empty your wallet.
Will go again soon.
My wife and I have attended two wine tasting dinners at Tommy V's previously and they we're also excellent -with very generous pours.
Do yourself a favor and check to see when Zoran will next host another wine tasting dinner and bring some friends- you'll be sure to enjoy.
Bob - Paradise Valley, AZ

